# SHA256 checksums for all source dependencies
# Ref: SLSA Level 2 requirement - verified source integrity
# Ref: Cyber Resilience Act Article 47 - supply chain integrity
#
# IMPORTANT: These checksums MUST be updated when dependency versions change.
# Run `make verify-checksums` to regenerate after version updates.
#
# Format: <sha256> <component>:<version>
# When a checksum is empty, the download will proceed but log a warning.
# Fill in checksums after first verified download of each new version.
#
# To generate checksums for a new version:
#   curl -sL <url> | sha256sum
#
# NOTE: Checksums are version-dependent. When generate-deps-env.py updates
# versions, these checksums must be refreshed. The CI pipeline will warn
# (but not fail) on missing checksums to allow version bumps, and will
# hard-fail on checksum mismatches to catch tampering.
